<2ND_LINE>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0390</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Thunderstorms Rumble Through South</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Thunderstorms rumbled through Arkansas, west Texas, from Florida
to the middle Mississippi Valley, through New England and western
Washington today while skies over much of the nation were clear.
   A half dozen thunderstorms stirred up severe weather in the
South on Friday night. In Arkansas, thunderstorms whipped high
winds that downed power lines in Little Rock and blew a
tractor-trailer off the interstate highway east of Mayflower. A
thunderstorm in Alabama produced high winds that downed trees and
power lines around Mobile.
   Today's forecast called for scattered showers and thunderstorms
from the lower Missouri Valley through western, lower Tennessee
Valley and central Gulf Coast into central and southern Florida;
scattered showers across northern and central New England and
through the northern Pacific coast; and mostly sunny skies over the
rest of the nation.
   Temperatures were forecast in the 70s or 80s across much of the
nation; in the 60s across the northern two-thirds of New England
and over northwest Washington; in the 90s from the northern Rockies
through the central and southern inter-mountain regions, across
central and eastern Texas into the lower Mississippi Valley and
across the southern half of Florida; between 100 and 105 across the
Rio Grande Valleys of Texas; between 100 and 110 degrees from the
valleys of California into the desert Southwest.
   Temperatures around the nation at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 45
degrees at Marquette, Mich., Sault Ste Marie, Mich., and Traverse
City, Mich., to 89 degrees at Las Vegas, Nev.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 71 partly cloudy; Boston 53 cloudy; Buffalo 57
fair; Charleston, S.C. 67 foggy; Cincinnati 57 fair; Cleveland 50
fair; Detroit 54 fair; Miami 79 partly cloudy; New York 61 fair;
Philadelphia 57 fair; Pittsburgh 54 fair; Portland, Maine 52 partly
cloudy; Washington 62 fair.
   _Central: Bismarck 62 cloudy; Chicago 61 fair; Dallas-Fort Worth
83 fair; Denver 68 fair; Des Moines 64 cloudy; Indianapolis 63
cloudy; Kansas City 61 cloudy; Minneapolis-St. Paul 63 partly
cloudy; Nashville 66 cloudy; New Orleans 79 fair; St. Louis 69
cloudy.
   _West: Albuquerque 72 fair; Anchorage 57 cloudy; Las Vegas 89
fair; Phoenix 94 thunderstorms; Salt Lake City 77 partly cloudy;
San Diego 63 fair; San Francisco 55 fair; Seattle 58 rain.
   _Canada: Toronto 50 fair.
</TEXT>
