<1ST_LINE>r i PM-Korea-DMZ     07-02 0167</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Korea-DMZ,0173</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>North Korea Says South Attacked Its Border Guards</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   North Korea today accused South Korean troops of
attacking one of its border guardposts with machine-gun fire.
   The attack occurred south of Changpoong in the western end of
the Demilitarized Zone on Friday, Pyongyang's official Korean
Central News Agency said.
   It said the attack endangered the safety of North Korean
personnel, but it did not report if the communist nation's forces
fired back or if there were casualties.
   The agency said the attack constituted a grave military
provocation premeditated by South Korean authorities to increase
tension and cause military conflict. It said South Korea was
seeking an excuse to suppress anti-U.S. and anti-fascist domestic
movements.
   There was no immediate comment from South Korea.
   The two countries maintain more than 1 million heavily armed
troops facing each other along the 150-mile demarcation line which
runs across the waist of the Korean peninsula. It was established
under the 1953 armistice that ended the Korean War.
</TEXT>
