<HEAD>No Ifs, Ands or Butts</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WAILUKU, Hawaii (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   No ifs, ands or butts _ a man convicted
of stealing a load of cigarettes will have to kick the habit or
spend time behind bars.
   State Judge Boyd P. Mossman believes an addiction to cigarettes
caused Elroy T. Rin to steal $427 worth of them from a barge last
year at Kaunakakai Harbor on Molokai Island.
   Rin, 20, pleaded no contest to fourth-degree theft in connection
with the cigarette heist, and also to second-degree theft involving
$110 worth of stolen beer.
   At a sentencing hearing Friday, Mossman told Rin to avoid
alcohol and drug use and suspended a 90-day jail term on condition
that Rin quit smoking.
   Mossman also put Rin on five years probation, ordered him to
perform 300 hours of community service and told him to get a job.
