<HEAD>Six More Flood Deaths In Bangladesh</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DHAKA, Bangladesh (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Six more people drowned in floods
recently in Bangladesh, bringing the death toll in this year's
rainy season to 71, officials said Saturday.
   The latest deaths occurred Thursday and Friday. The victims _
three children and three adults _ drowned in flood waters in
Mymensingh district, 55 miles north of Dhaka, relief officials told
The Associated Press by telephone.
   At least 400,000 people have been affected in Mymensingh, most
of them farmers whose crops and homes have been submerged in floods
that ravage Bangladesh annually.
   An estimated 10 million people have been stranded, displaced or
otherwise affected by monsoon floods in Bangladesh this year.
   That's nearly 10 percent of the population of 105 million.
   Last year, about 1,200 people died in floods from the annual
monsoon rains, which last from April through July.
</TEXT>
