<2ND_LINE>AM-Israel-Heroin,0150</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Police Catch Heroin Pass On Border</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Israeli police intercepted a drug pass Saturday
when a Lebanese man threw a bundle containing 2.2 pounds of heroin
across Israel's northern border to a waiting accomplice, a police
spokeswoman said.
   Police in the northern region of Galilee arrested the man on the
Israeli side of the border, the spokeswoman said.
   The spokeswoman, who asked not to be identified, said the heroin
was worth ``hundreds of thousands of dollars,'' but she could not
specify the exact amount.
   ``Our detectives were scouting the area and they noticed a
Lebanese man throwing a package over the border,'' the spokewoman
said. ``Then they noticed the ... man waiting for it.''
   Israeli police have focused their attention on activity near the
border to try to stem the flow of drugs from Lebanon into Israel,
the spokeswoman said.
</TEXT>
