<HEAD>Storm Kills Four, Five Missing</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ANKARA, Turkey (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Three days of heavy rains in Turkey
triggered floods that killed three people and left five others
missing, news agencies reported Saturday.
   Two miners drowned Friday when flood waters poured into a coal
mine in the Black Sea coastal province of Zonguldak, the Anatolia
News Agency reported. An 85-year-old woman drowned in the eastern
province of Agri, the agency said.
   In addition, a shepherd was reported dead after being struck by
lightning in the eastern province of Erzurum.
   Five people were missing in Ordu province in the Black Sea
region after flood waters swept their jeep from a bridge, according
to Anatolia.
   The storms also flooded crops in the Ordu region, causing damage
estimated at $200,000, the agency said.
