<1ST_LINE>r i AM-Obit-Gradl     07-02 0133</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Obit-Gradl,0138</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Berlin CDU Co-Founder Dies at Age 84</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BERLIN (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Johann Baptist Gradl, a former federal government
minister and respected West Berlin politician, died following a
long illness, city officials said Saturday. Gradl was 84.
   Gradl, who died late Friday night, helped found Berlin's
Christian Democratic Union party in 1945.
   He fled the Soviet-controlled sector of the divided city into
West Berlin two years later, after disagreements with communist
authorities.
   Gradl was a member of the West German parliament, the Bundestag,
from 1957 to 1980, representing West Berlin.
   He also served as the federal minister for German exiles in
1965-66.
   From 1969 to 1972, he was chairman of the Bundestag Committee
for German-German Relations.
   West German Chancellor Helmut Kohl on Saturday said Gradl had
``devoted his life to German reunification.''
</TEXT>
