<HEAD>Report 1,400 Arrested In Anti-Crime Sweep</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-South Africa-Bomb</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JOHANNESBURG, South Africa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   More than 1,400 people have
been arrested during the past several days in a nationwide
anti-crime sweep, police reported Saturday.
   They said those detained were suspected of crimes ranging from
murder, armed robbery and burglary to possession of marijuana.
   The report did not say if any of the prisoners were accused of
involvement in politically related crimes.
   It gave give this account:
   Some 1,200 suspects were arrested in Cape Town and the
surrounding area this week, including 650 people taken into custody
Friday.
   There were at least 200 arrests in Pretoria and nearby towns.
   More than 2,000 policemen were assigned to anti-crime operations
in the Johannesburg area Friday and Saturday but no arrest figures
were immediately available.
