<HEAD>Scottish Coast Guard Rescues Icelanders From Yacht</HEAD>
<DATELINE>STORNOWAY, Scotland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A coast guard helicopter on Saturday
rescued four Icelanders from a yacht in heavy seas off the remote
Outer Hebrides Islands of western Scotland, the coast guard
reported.
   The 28-foot yacht radioed a distress call after it lost its life
raft and much of its gear in wind-whipped seas, said Jim Budge of
the Stornoway coast guard.
   He said rescuers dropped from the helicopter and lifted the four
Icelanders off the yacht one by one about 45 miles northwest of St.
Kilda in the Hebrides.
   A French trawler had responded to the yacht's distress call but
was unable to rescue the crew because of the storm, according to
Budge.
   He said the Icelanders had been headed for home from the
Scottish island of Coll. He did not have the name of the vessel.
