<HEAD>``Little Massimo'' Wins Siena Palio</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SIENA, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Jockey Massimo Coghe rode Benito to victory
Saturday in the Palio, a medieval-style bareback race around
Siena's main plaza.
   Three horses fell during the race, known for its rough style and
intense rivalry. One of the animals broke a leg and was destroyed
after the race.
   The race, which dates to 1260, is run in July and August
following religious holidays.
   Coghe, nicknamed ``Little Massimo,'' was riding for Il Nicchio
(The Shell) club. It was the club's 41st victory.
   Animal rights groups have called for the Palio race to be banned
because they say it is cruel to animals.
